WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.200
Cambridge English readers level one next door to love by Margaret Johnson

00:30.000 --> 00:56.800
Chapter 1 The Man at Number 3

00:56.800 --> 01:01.040
My friend Janet looked out of my living room window.

01:01.040 --> 01:03.520
Who is that?

01:03.520 --> 01:05.000
She asked.

01:05.000 --> 01:07.440
I went to look.

01:07.440 --> 01:10.280
He lives here, I said.

01:10.280 --> 01:13.360
He lives here in Bridge Street.

01:13.360 --> 01:14.560
Janet asked.

01:14.560 --> 01:16.960
Yes, I said.

01:16.960 --> 01:20.120
At Number 3, next door to me.

01:20.120 --> 01:22.720
He's my new neighbor.

01:22.720 --> 01:23.720
Janet smiled.

01:23.720 --> 01:26.560
He's very tall.

01:26.560 --> 01:28.080
She said.

01:28.080 --> 01:30.320
And I like his black hair.

01:30.320 --> 01:33.280
Janet, I said.

01:33.280 --> 01:35.800
Come away from the window.

01:35.800 --> 01:39.320
I didn't want my new neighbor to see us.

01:39.320 --> 01:41.120
She turned to me.

01:41.120 --> 01:42.600
It's okay.

01:42.600 --> 01:43.600
She said.

01:43.600 --> 01:45.800
I'm just looking.

01:45.800 --> 01:47.880
I don't want a new man.

01:47.880 --> 01:50.320
I've got David.

01:50.320 --> 01:52.480
David is Janet's boyfriend.

01:53.200 --> 01:57.120
I'm only thinking of you, she said.

01:57.120 --> 02:00.360
You need a new boyfriend.

02:00.360 --> 02:02.440
What's your neighbor's job?

02:02.440 --> 02:04.120
She asked me.

02:04.120 --> 02:07.360
I don't know, I said.

02:07.360 --> 02:10.440
Well, how old is he?

02:10.440 --> 02:12.360
I looked at her.

02:12.360 --> 02:16.520
I don't know Janet, I said.

02:16.520 --> 02:19.160
Has he got a girlfriend?

02:19.160 --> 02:21.960
Janet, I said.

02:22.040 --> 02:25.240
I don't know anything about him.

02:25.240 --> 02:29.080
I saw him yesterday and we said, hello.

02:29.080 --> 02:30.840
That's all.

02:30.840 --> 02:35.760
Janet always wanted me to go out and meet new men.

02:35.760 --> 02:40.280
You need to go out, Stella, she often told me.

02:40.280 --> 02:42.760
You need to meet new people.

02:42.760 --> 02:45.400
New men.

02:45.400 --> 02:48.600
But I didn't want to meet new men.

02:48.600 --> 02:51.280
And I didn't want a boyfriend.

02:51.280 --> 02:55.680
I knew boyfriends didn't always make you happy.

02:55.680 --> 03:00.800
My last boyfriend, James, didn't make me happy.

03:00.800 --> 03:03.160
Janet looked at me.

03:03.160 --> 03:07.000
You're thinking about James, she said.

03:07.000 --> 03:10.320
Janet often knows what I'm thinking.

03:10.320 --> 03:13.920
Don't think about him, she said.

03:13.920 --> 03:17.000
He wasn't any good for you.

03:17.000 --> 03:20.640
But you mustn't think all men are bad.

03:20.640 --> 03:23.360
Your neighbor looks nice.

03:23.360 --> 03:30.200
Stop talking about him, I told her, and we laughed.

03:30.200 --> 03:34.280
Janet left my house at about six o'clock

03:34.280 --> 03:38.040
and I went up to change for my tennis class.

03:38.040 --> 03:40.920
My neighbor was out in his garden.

03:40.920 --> 03:43.960
It was August and there were lots of flowers

03:43.960 --> 03:46.120
in all the gardens.

03:46.120 --> 03:48.960
The flowers in the garden at number three

03:48.960 --> 03:52.960
were yellow, red, orange, and pink.

03:52.960 --> 03:55.120
Happy colors.

03:55.120 --> 03:59.200
But my neighbor didn't look happy.

03:59.200 --> 04:03.960
You're sad, I thought, as I looked down at him.

04:03.960 --> 04:05.840
Why?

04:05.840 --> 04:08.440
Why are you sad?

04:08.440 --> 04:14.520
Then he looked up and I came away from the window quickly.

04:14.520 --> 04:18.760
I saw my neighbor again the next morning in the street.

04:18.760 --> 04:20.960
He looked tired.

04:20.960 --> 04:23.120
Hello, I said.

04:23.120 --> 04:26.480
It's a beautiful day.

04:26.480 --> 04:28.880
Yes, he said.

04:28.880 --> 04:32.560
It's hot again, too hot for work.

04:32.560 --> 04:35.360
Then he smiled at me.

04:35.360 --> 04:38.200
My name's Tony, he said.

04:38.200 --> 04:42.160
Tony Bryant, I took his hand.

04:42.160 --> 04:44.800
Hello, Tony, I said.

04:44.800 --> 04:48.560
I'm Stella, Stella Greenwood.

04:48.560 --> 04:52.560
Good to meet you, Stella, he said.

04:52.560 --> 04:57.720
I didn't see Tony the next day, all the day after that.

04:57.720 --> 05:03.400
Then on the Friday morning, I heard him on the phone next door.

05:03.400 --> 05:06.040
The houses in Bridge Street are small

05:06.040 --> 05:09.640
and you can sometimes hear people speaking.

05:09.640 --> 05:14.760
And I heard everything that Tony Bryant said that morning.

05:14.760 --> 05:16.920
He was very angry.

05:16.920 --> 05:21.000
You can't do this, Cathy, he said.

05:21.000 --> 05:24.160
You can't do this to me again.

05:24.160 --> 05:26.240
I want to see her.

05:26.240 --> 05:30.400
Please, Cathy, don't do this.

05:30.400 --> 05:34.600
I sat at my breakfast table and listened.

05:34.600 --> 05:40.880
Cathy, Cathy, oh, I heard Tony say.

05:40.880 --> 05:44.240
And then he put the phone down.

05:44.240 --> 05:48.440
I ate an apple and thought about Tony Bryant.

05:48.440 --> 05:50.560
Who was Cathy?

05:50.560 --> 05:53.360
And what was Tony afraid of?

05:53.360 --> 05:58.000
Because I knew he was afraid of something.

05:58.000 --> 06:01.280
There's something Janet always says to me,

06:01.280 --> 06:04.400
something that's very important to her.

06:04.400 --> 06:09.800
She says, when you want to do something, just do it.

06:09.800 --> 06:12.240
Don't stop and think about it.

06:12.240 --> 06:13.520
Don't wait.

06:13.520 --> 06:15.400
Just do it.

06:15.400 --> 06:20.400
And that's what I did after I heard Tony Bryant on the phone.

06:20.400 --> 06:25.120
I didn't stop and think I put my apple down on the table

06:25.120 --> 06:27.960
and went to the house next door.

06:27.960 --> 06:30.360
I had to wait a long time.

06:30.360 --> 06:33.280
Then Tony answered the door.

06:33.280 --> 06:35.920
Yes, he said.

06:35.920 --> 06:38.160
He didn't look very happy.

06:38.160 --> 06:42.920
And then, of course, I didn't know what to say.

06:42.920 --> 06:46.200
Yes, he said again.

06:46.200 --> 06:48.840
What do you want, Stella?

06:48.840 --> 06:53.920
I started to blush then, and my face felt hot.

06:53.920 --> 07:01.520
I wanted, I started to say, I just wanted to know,

07:01.520 --> 07:03.280
and I stopped.

07:03.280 --> 07:08.120
You wanted to know what, Tony said.

07:08.120 --> 07:11.240
Well, are you all right?

07:11.240 --> 07:14.320
I asked, and he looked at me.

07:14.320 --> 07:19.920
His face was cold, but I thought he was just sad or angry

07:19.920 --> 07:22.600
about something.

07:22.600 --> 07:24.160
Yes, thank you.

07:24.160 --> 07:27.760
He said, I'm all right.

07:27.760 --> 07:29.960
I blushed some more.

07:29.960 --> 07:32.760
Oh, I said.

07:32.760 --> 07:34.040
OK.

07:34.040 --> 07:35.240
Good.

07:35.240 --> 07:36.840
That's good.

07:36.840 --> 07:38.000
Good.

07:38.000 --> 07:43.720
Well, by then, and I left quickly,

07:43.720 --> 07:47.120
but then Tony called after me.

07:47.120 --> 07:49.800
Stella, wait.

07:49.800 --> 07:54.120
I stopped and looked back at him.

07:54.120 --> 07:57.400
I'm sorry, he said.

07:57.400 --> 08:00.320
It was nice of you to ask.

08:00.320 --> 08:03.640
Have you got time to come in for a coffee?

08:03.640 --> 08:05.680
I looked at my watch.

08:05.680 --> 08:08.080
It was 9 o'clock.

08:08.080 --> 08:10.680
Not now, I said.

08:10.680 --> 08:12.320
Sorry, Tony.

08:12.320 --> 08:14.640
I'm late for work.

08:14.640 --> 08:17.000
OK, he said.

08:17.000 --> 08:22.320
I'm going away today, but come for coffee next weekend.

08:22.320 --> 08:24.520
I smiled at him.

08:24.520 --> 08:26.080
Thank you, I said.

08:26.080 --> 08:34.080
Chapter 2, Flowers from Daisy.

08:34.080 --> 08:39.080
The next weekend, it was hot again,

08:39.080 --> 08:43.080
and I wanted to sit in the sun all day.

08:43.080 --> 08:47.080
I took a book and a drink and went out into the garden.

08:47.080 --> 08:51.080
And that's when I heard the child.

08:51.080 --> 08:55.080
I'm going out, the child said.

08:55.080 --> 09:00.080
And then a small face looked at me from Tony's garden.

09:00.080 --> 09:02.080
A little girl's face.

09:02.080 --> 09:06.080
Hello, the little girl said to me.

09:06.080 --> 09:10.080
She had lots of black hair under her big sun hat.

09:10.080 --> 09:13.080
Hello, I said.

09:13.080 --> 09:15.080
Who are you?

09:15.080 --> 09:18.080
Daisy, she said.

09:18.080 --> 09:20.080
That's a flower.

09:20.080 --> 09:22.080
I like flowers.

09:22.080 --> 09:24.080
Do you like flowers?

09:25.080 --> 09:27.080
I smiled at her.

09:27.080 --> 09:33.080
She was about five or six years old, but who was she?

09:33.080 --> 09:35.080
Then Tony came out.

09:35.080 --> 09:40.080
He stood next to Daisy, and I knew who she was.

09:40.080 --> 09:43.080
Hello, he said to me.

09:43.080 --> 09:46.080
This is my daughter, Daisy.

09:46.080 --> 09:49.080
Hello, Daisy, I said.

09:49.080 --> 09:52.080
And I saw that Tony was happy.

09:52.080 --> 09:55.080
Very happy.

09:55.080 --> 09:58.080
Can she come to tea with us, Daddy?

09:58.080 --> 10:01.080
Daisy asked her father.

10:01.080 --> 10:05.080
She has a name, Tony told her.

10:05.080 --> 10:07.080
She's called Stella.

10:07.080 --> 10:11.080
Okay, can Stella come to tea with us?

10:11.080 --> 10:13.080
Daisy asked.

10:13.080 --> 10:15.080
Tony smiled at me.

10:15.080 --> 10:19.080
Of course she can, he said.

10:19.080 --> 10:24.080
We sat in Tony's garden, and Daisy told me all about her cat.

10:24.080 --> 10:27.080
She talked a lot.

10:27.080 --> 10:30.080
He's black and white, she said.

10:30.080 --> 10:32.080
Like a cow.

10:32.080 --> 10:36.080
I call him Moo Moo, like the noise cows make.

10:36.080 --> 10:38.080
But he drinks milk.

10:38.080 --> 10:41.080
Cows don't drink milk.

10:41.080 --> 10:43.080
Cows make milk.

10:43.080 --> 10:45.080
Tony told her.

10:45.080 --> 10:48.080
He smiled at me over Daisy's head.

10:48.080 --> 10:50.080
Daisy looked at him.

10:50.080 --> 10:54.080
I know that, Daddy, she said.

10:54.080 --> 10:57.080
I'm not a little girl anymore.

10:57.080 --> 11:00.080
And she went to look at the flowers.

11:00.080 --> 11:04.080
She's lovely, I told Tony.

11:04.080 --> 11:08.080
He looked at his daughter and smiled.

11:08.080 --> 11:10.080
Yes, he said.

11:10.080 --> 11:12.080
She is.

11:12.080 --> 11:15.080
Then he looked sad.

11:15.080 --> 11:21.080
But I don't see her very often, because her mother and I aren't together now.

11:21.080 --> 11:25.080
That's why he's sad, I thought.

11:25.080 --> 11:29.080
I'm sorry, Tony, I said.

11:29.080 --> 11:34.080
I'm okay now, Tony said quickly.

11:34.080 --> 11:36.080
He smiled at me.

11:36.080 --> 11:39.080
Anyway, how are you?

11:39.080 --> 11:41.080
How was your week?

11:41.080 --> 11:44.080
It was good, I said.

11:44.080 --> 11:46.080
There was a lot to do at work.

11:46.080 --> 11:48.080
Tony smiled.

11:48.080 --> 11:51.080
What do you do?

11:51.080 --> 11:56.080
I'm one of the cooks at Marcello's Italian restaurant.

11:56.080 --> 11:59.080
You're a chef, he said.

11:59.080 --> 12:01.080
That's a good job.

12:01.080 --> 12:03.080
Yes, I said.

12:03.080 --> 12:05.080
I love it.

12:05.080 --> 12:06.080
What about you?

12:06.080 --> 12:08.080
What do you do?

12:08.080 --> 12:12.080
I work with computers, Tony told me.

12:12.080 --> 12:15.080
Daisy came over to us again.

12:15.080 --> 12:18.080
These are for you, she said.

12:18.080 --> 12:21.080
And she gave us some flowers.

12:21.080 --> 12:24.080
Thank you, Daisy, we said.

12:24.080 --> 12:29.080
She smiled at us and then ran away across the garden.

12:29.080 --> 12:33.080
Leave some flowers in the garden, please, Daisy.

12:33.080 --> 12:35.080
Tony told her.

12:35.080 --> 12:37.080
They looked nice there.

12:37.080 --> 12:41.080
I put my face into the red and orange flowers.

12:41.080 --> 12:43.080
They were beautiful.

12:43.080 --> 12:47.080
I think she likes you, Tony told me.

12:47.080 --> 12:49.080
I smiled at him.

12:49.080 --> 12:51.080
I like her too.

12:51.080 --> 12:55.080
Tony looked at the flowers in his hand.

12:55.080 --> 13:01.080
Some of me dies when Daisy's away from me, he said.

13:01.080 --> 13:03.080
Then he looked at me.

13:03.080 --> 13:09.080
Daisy lives with her mother, Kathy, and Kathy's husband, Cameron.

13:09.080 --> 13:11.080
Tony looked away.

13:11.080 --> 13:16.080
Daisy's got a new family now, he said.

13:16.080 --> 13:19.080
Well, now I knew.

13:19.080 --> 13:24.080
Kathy, the woman on the phone was Daisy's mother.

13:24.080 --> 13:27.080
That's sad, I said.

13:27.080 --> 13:31.080
Tony smiled, but he wasn't happy.

13:31.080 --> 13:35.080
Yes, oh, I know Daisy likes Cameron.

13:35.080 --> 13:37.080
But he isn't her father.

13:37.080 --> 13:39.080
I am.

13:39.080 --> 13:42.080
How often do you see Daisy?

13:42.080 --> 13:44.080
I asked.

13:44.080 --> 13:46.080
Not very often.

13:46.080 --> 13:49.080
But she sees Cameron every day.

13:49.080 --> 13:53.080
Anyway, she's here today, Tony said.

13:53.080 --> 13:55.080
And I'm happy.

13:55.080 --> 13:58.080
Daisy looked over and smiled at us.

13:58.080 --> 14:02.080
I smiled back at her.

14:02.080 --> 14:06.080
I can understand computers, Tony told me.

14:06.080 --> 14:09.080
I know what they're going to do.

14:09.080 --> 14:13.080
But I don't always understand people.

14:13.080 --> 14:18.080
I thought about James and all his girlfriends.

14:18.080 --> 14:24.080
No, we don't always know what people are going to do, I said.

14:24.080 --> 14:28.080
Next day, I met up with Janet in town.

14:28.080 --> 14:31.080
We went to a cafe for a drink.

14:31.080 --> 14:33.080
She asked about Tony.

14:33.080 --> 14:37.080
And I told her about my afternoon with him.

14:37.080 --> 14:40.080
Did he ask you to go out with him?

14:40.080 --> 14:42.080
She wanted to know.

14:42.080 --> 14:44.080
No, I said.

14:44.080 --> 14:47.080
He's just my neighbour.

14:47.080 --> 14:50.080
But I blushed and Janet saw.

14:50.080 --> 14:53.080
You like him, she told me.

14:53.080 --> 14:56.080
Yes, all right, I said.

14:56.080 --> 14:59.080
I do like him.

14:59.080 --> 15:02.080
But he's a very sad man.

15:02.080 --> 15:06.080
I think he's still in love with Daisy's mother, Kathy.

15:06.080 --> 15:09.080
Janet looked at me.

15:09.080 --> 15:13.080
But you said Kathy is Cameron's wife now?

15:13.080 --> 15:15.080
Yes, I said.

15:15.080 --> 15:18.080
Kathy is Cameron's wife.

15:18.080 --> 15:22.080
But Tony still thinks about the time when they were a family.

15:22.080 --> 15:25.080
Him, Daisy and Kathy.

15:25.080 --> 15:29.080
I don't think he understands why everything changed.

15:29.080 --> 15:33.080
That is sad, Janet said.

15:33.080 --> 15:35.080
Then she looked at me.

15:35.080 --> 15:40.080
Well, she said, you need a man to laugh with.

15:40.080 --> 15:43.080
So I don't think Tony is good for you.

15:43.080 --> 15:46.080
I don't need a man, Janet.

15:46.080 --> 15:48.080
I told her.

15:48.080 --> 15:51.080
I'm happy without a boyfriend.

15:51.080 --> 15:53.080
But Janet looked at me.

15:53.080 --> 16:02.080
Everybody needs someone stellar, she said.

16:02.080 --> 16:04.080
Chapter 3.

16:04.080 --> 16:08.080
Everybody needs someone.

16:08.080 --> 16:15.080
The next day, lots of people came to Marcello's restaurant and I had lots of food to cook.

16:15.080 --> 16:22.080
The weather was still warm and in the kitchen it was very, very hot.

16:22.080 --> 16:25.080
I was happy to have lots to do.

16:25.080 --> 16:29.080
I didn't want to think about Janet's words.

16:29.080 --> 16:33.080
Everybody needs someone stellar.

16:33.080 --> 16:38.080
But of course, I did think about them all day.

16:38.080 --> 16:44.080
I also thought about James and how he made me sad.

16:44.080 --> 16:49.080
Then I thought about Tony and how Kathy made him sad.

16:49.080 --> 16:51.080
And then Daisy.

16:51.080 --> 16:54.080
They all enjoyed their food.

16:54.080 --> 16:57.080
Klaus, one of the waiters told me in the afternoon.

16:57.080 --> 16:59.080
I liked Klaus.

16:59.080 --> 17:05.080
He was over in England from Germany for six months and he was always happy.

17:05.080 --> 17:08.080
Good, I replied.

17:08.080 --> 17:11.080
Do you want to go out with me tonight, stellar?

17:11.080 --> 17:13.080
Klaus asked me.

17:13.080 --> 17:17.080
I'm going to the cinema. Can you come?

17:17.080 --> 17:20.080
I thought about Janet's words again.

17:20.080 --> 17:24.080
Everybody needs someone, stellar.

17:24.080 --> 17:27.080
Then I looked at Klaus and smiled.

17:27.080 --> 17:30.080
Yes, okay, I said.

17:30.080 --> 17:36.080
When I got home at six o'clock, Tony was taking things out of his car.

17:36.080 --> 17:39.080
Hi, stellar, he said.

17:39.080 --> 17:41.080
I smiled at him.

17:41.080 --> 17:45.080
He looked good in his black work trousers and white shirt.

17:45.080 --> 17:48.080
Hi, Tony. How are you?

17:48.080 --> 17:51.080
Very well, thank you, he replied.

17:51.080 --> 17:54.080
It's good to see you.

17:54.080 --> 17:56.080
Yes, I said.

17:56.080 --> 17:58.080
It's good to see you too.

17:58.080 --> 18:02.080
I'm going out for a drink tonight, he said.

18:02.080 --> 18:04.080
At the tree house bar.

18:04.080 --> 18:07.080
He looked at me.

18:07.080 --> 18:10.080
Do you want to come with me, stellar?

18:10.080 --> 18:12.080
I stopped smiling.

18:12.080 --> 18:15.080
Oh, I replied.

18:15.080 --> 18:18.080
I can't. I'm sorry, Tony.

18:18.080 --> 18:21.080
I'm going to the cinema tonight.

18:21.080 --> 18:24.080
That's okay, Tony said.

18:24.080 --> 18:26.080
And he walked to his house.

18:26.080 --> 18:31.080
I looked at Tony's back as he opened his front door.

18:31.080 --> 18:35.080
I didn't want to go to the cinema with Klaus now.

18:35.080 --> 18:39.080
I wanted to go out for a drink with Tony.

18:39.080 --> 18:43.080
How about tomorrow night? I asked.

18:43.080 --> 18:47.080
Tony looked back at me and smiled.

18:47.080 --> 18:50.080
Okay, he said.

18:50.080 --> 18:54.080
Good. Eight o'clock then?

18:54.080 --> 18:56.080
I smiled at him.

18:56.080 --> 19:00.080
Eight o'clock tomorrow, I replied.

19:00.080 --> 19:03.080
I enjoyed going out with Klaus.

19:03.080 --> 19:07.080
The film was called Dead Men Can't Speak.

19:07.080 --> 19:12.080
It was a very bad film, but it made me and Klaus laugh.

19:12.080 --> 19:15.080
I need a drink after that.

19:15.080 --> 19:17.080
Klaus said when we came out.

19:17.080 --> 19:21.080
And we went to a bar near the cinema.

19:21.080 --> 19:24.080
Sorry about the film, Stella.

19:24.080 --> 19:27.080
He said when we had our drinks.

19:27.080 --> 19:32.080
Next time we can go to a film you want to see.

19:32.080 --> 19:35.080
But I just smiled and drank my drink.

19:35.080 --> 19:41.080
I liked Klaus, but I didn't want to think about next time now.

19:42.080 --> 19:46.080
After the bar, Klaus walked home with me.

19:46.080 --> 19:50.080
I knew he wanted me to ask him into the house.

19:50.080 --> 19:52.080
But I didn't.

19:52.080 --> 19:56.080
Thank you for tonight, Klaus. I said.

19:56.080 --> 20:01.080
I enjoyed it. See you tomorrow at work.

20:01.080 --> 20:06.080
I think he was a little sad, but he smiled anyway.

20:06.080 --> 20:11.080
Okay, Stella, he said. See you tomorrow.

20:11.080 --> 20:13.080
I opened my front door.

20:13.080 --> 20:18.080
Stella, Klaus said behind me, and I looked at him.

20:18.080 --> 20:23.080
Yes? I like you a lot.

20:23.080 --> 20:27.080
Thank you, I said. Good night.

20:27.080 --> 20:31.080
Then I went into my house and closed the door.

20:32.080 --> 20:36.080
I didn't say, I like you too, Klaus.

20:36.080 --> 20:39.080
Because I didn't know what I thought.

20:39.080 --> 20:41.080
I liked him.

20:41.080 --> 20:44.080
But did I want to be his girlfriend?

20:44.080 --> 20:50.080
Or just his friend?

20:50.080 --> 20:52.080
Chapter four.

20:52.080 --> 20:55.080
Drinks for two.

20:55.080 --> 20:59.080
When I got home from work the next evening,

20:59.080 --> 21:04.080
I washed my hair and put on a new dress.

21:04.080 --> 21:09.080
You look nice, Tony told me when we met at eight o'clock.

21:09.080 --> 21:12.080
Thank you, I said.

21:12.080 --> 21:16.080
Tony's blue shard was like the blue of his eyes.

21:16.080 --> 21:19.080
He looked good too.

21:19.080 --> 21:21.080
Bring your jacket.

21:21.080 --> 21:24.080
Then we can sit out, he said.

21:24.080 --> 21:28.080
I got a jacket, and then we left.

21:28.080 --> 21:30.080
I love warm evenings.

21:30.080 --> 21:33.080
Tony said as we walked down the street.

21:33.080 --> 21:37.080
When I first met Cathy, we lived in Scotland.

21:37.080 --> 21:41.080
It gets dark at eleven o'clock there at this time of year.

21:41.080 --> 21:45.080
I loved the long evenings.

21:45.080 --> 21:49.080
I didn't say anything, and he looked at me.

21:49.080 --> 21:52.080
Sorry, he said.

21:52.080 --> 21:55.080
I know I talk about the old days a lot.

21:55.080 --> 21:58.080
That's okay, I said.

21:58.080 --> 22:00.080
No, he said.

22:00.080 --> 22:02.080
It isn't okay.

22:02.080 --> 22:05.080
I don't want to think about the old days tonight.

22:05.080 --> 22:09.080
I just want to think about now.

22:09.080 --> 22:11.080
I was happy to hear that.

22:11.080 --> 22:17.080
And when I smiled at him, he smiled back.

22:17.080 --> 22:22.080
I want to know everything about you, Stella, he told me.

22:22.080 --> 22:25.080
Everything, I asked.

22:25.080 --> 22:27.080
Yes, he said.

22:27.080 --> 22:30.080
Everything.

22:30.080 --> 22:34.080
There were lots of people in the garden at the treehouse bar.

22:34.080 --> 22:39.080
Men and women sitting at small tables having conversations.

22:39.080 --> 22:41.080
Couples.

22:41.080 --> 22:46.080
And when Tony and I sat at a table, we were a couple too.

22:46.080 --> 22:48.080
I like it here.

22:48.080 --> 22:50.080
Tony said.

22:50.080 --> 22:53.080
Yes, I said.

22:53.080 --> 22:55.080
I do too.

22:55.080 --> 22:58.080
Tony had his drink in his hand.

22:58.080 --> 23:00.080
He smiled at me.

23:00.080 --> 23:04.080
He is to good neighbors, he said.

23:04.080 --> 23:07.080
To good neighbors.

23:07.080 --> 23:10.080
Then Tony looked at me.

23:10.080 --> 23:15.080
Tell me about your job, he said.

23:15.080 --> 23:18.080
What food do you like to cook?

23:18.080 --> 23:21.080
I thought about it.

23:21.080 --> 23:25.080
Food with lots of color, I said.

23:25.080 --> 23:28.080
I like my meals to look good.

23:28.080 --> 23:31.080
That's very important to me.

23:31.080 --> 23:34.080
I must come and eat at your restaurant.

23:34.080 --> 23:36.080
Tony said.

23:36.080 --> 23:39.080
I spoke quickly without thinking.

23:39.080 --> 23:43.080
Or I can cook for you at home, I said.

23:43.080 --> 23:45.080
Tony smiled.

23:45.080 --> 23:49.080
Yes, please, he said.

23:49.080 --> 23:53.080
I love my job, I told him.

23:53.080 --> 23:57.080
When I was a child, I cooked with my mother.

23:57.080 --> 24:00.080
Daisy likes to cook with her mother.

24:00.080 --> 24:02.080
Tony told me.

24:02.080 --> 24:05.080
His face went sad.

24:05.080 --> 24:07.080
They make cakes.

24:07.080 --> 24:10.080
Kathy's a good cook too.

24:10.080 --> 24:12.080
I looked at him.

24:12.080 --> 24:14.080
What does Kathy do?

24:14.080 --> 24:16.080
I asked.

24:16.080 --> 24:20.080
She's a teacher, he told me.

24:20.080 --> 24:23.080
But I don't want to talk about Kathy.

24:23.080 --> 24:27.080
Tell me about you, your family.

24:27.080 --> 24:30.080
Where do they live?

24:30.080 --> 24:33.080
I told him and he listened.

24:33.080 --> 24:36.080
But I felt there were three people at the table now.

24:36.080 --> 24:40.080
Me, Tony and Kathy.

24:40.080 --> 24:45.080
I stopped talking about my family and looked at him.

24:45.080 --> 24:50.080
Tell me about you and Kathy, I said.

24:50.080 --> 24:53.080
Tony looked down at his drink.

24:53.080 --> 24:56.080
Kathy left me.

24:56.080 --> 25:00.080
She met Cameron at work, he said.

25:00.080 --> 25:05.080
She left me because she wanted to be with him.

25:05.080 --> 25:09.080
I loved someone too, I told him.

25:09.080 --> 25:15.080
James, but he had lots of girlfriends.

25:15.080 --> 25:20.080
Tony put his hand on mine.

25:20.080 --> 25:23.080
Do you want to meet someone new?

25:23.080 --> 25:25.080
He asked.

25:25.080 --> 25:27.080
I don't know.

25:27.080 --> 25:30.080
I said, I'm afraid.

25:30.080 --> 25:33.080
He smiled at me.

25:33.080 --> 25:38.080
Well, I'm also afraid, he said.

25:38.080 --> 25:41.080
But I do like you, Stella.

25:41.080 --> 25:44.080
I like you a lot.

25:44.080 --> 25:48.080
And I like you, Tony, I said.

25:48.080 --> 25:53.080
As I looked at him, I knew how I felt about Klaus.

25:53.080 --> 25:57.080
Klaus and I were friends, that was all.

25:57.080 --> 26:01.080
I liked him and I laughed with him.

26:01.080 --> 26:07.080
But when Klaus looked at me, I didn't feel like this.

26:07.080 --> 26:11.080
Tony looked into my eyes.

26:11.080 --> 26:14.080
Good, he said.

26:14.080 --> 26:17.080
Then come to tea at the weekend.

26:17.080 --> 26:20.080
Daisy told me she wants to see you again.

26:20.080 --> 26:24.080
And I want to see you again too.

26:24.080 --> 26:28.080
I went to tea with them on Sunday.

26:28.080 --> 26:31.080
We played football and got very hot.

26:31.080 --> 26:36.080
Then, when Daisy was in bed, Tony and I

26:36.080 --> 26:38.080
went into the garden.

26:38.080 --> 26:43.080
We sat and talked and Tony took my hand in his.

26:43.080 --> 26:49.080
And then I looked up at him and he kissed me.

26:49.080 --> 26:55.080
The next day, Klaus asked me to see a film with him again.

26:55.080 --> 26:58.080
But I told him I couldn't go.

26:58.080 --> 27:04.080
And when I met Janet for lunch, I told her about me and Tony.

27:04.080 --> 27:08.080
Everything's going very well, I said.

27:08.080 --> 27:12.080
Tony makes me very happy.

27:12.080 --> 27:15.080
She looked at me.

27:15.080 --> 27:18.080
Does he talk about Cathy when he's with you?

27:18.080 --> 27:21.080
She asked.

27:21.080 --> 27:26.080
He has to see Cathy because of Daisy, I told her.

27:26.080 --> 27:28.080
But that's all.

27:28.080 --> 27:31.080
Good, Janet said.

27:31.080 --> 27:33.080
But she didn't smile.

27:33.080 --> 27:36.080
I looked at her.

27:36.080 --> 27:39.080
It's okay, Janet, I said.

27:39.080 --> 27:42.080
Tony's a good man.

27:42.080 --> 27:45.080
He wants to be with me.

27:45.080 --> 27:49.080
Good, said Janet again.

27:49.080 --> 27:53.080
Because I only want you to be happy, Stella.

27:53.080 --> 27:56.080
And I was happy.

27:56.080 --> 28:00.080
For two months, I saw Tony every day.

28:00.080 --> 28:07.080
Sometimes Daisy was with us and sometimes it was just me and Tony.

28:07.080 --> 28:14.080
We went to see films, we walked in the park and I cooked meals for him.

28:14.080 --> 28:17.080
We talked and laughed a lot.

28:17.080 --> 28:22.080
Oh yes, I was very happy.

28:22.080 --> 28:29.080
And then one evening in October, everything changed.

28:29.080 --> 28:35.080
I left work to walk home and I saw James in a bar.

28:35.080 --> 28:37.080
He was with a woman.

28:37.080 --> 28:42.080
They were laughing and they looked happy.

28:42.080 --> 28:47.080
He laughed with me like that when he was my boyfriend.

28:47.080 --> 28:49.080
I thought.

28:49.080 --> 28:53.080
And I wanted to go into the restaurant to talk to the woman.

28:53.080 --> 28:59.080
I wanted to say to her, James is no good.

28:59.080 --> 29:01.080
But I didn't.

29:01.080 --> 29:04.080
I just walked up the street.

29:04.080 --> 29:08.080
But I was sad for her.

29:08.080 --> 29:15.080
Then when I got back to Bridge Street, I saw Tony in front of his house.

29:15.080 --> 29:18.080
He was with a woman too.

29:18.080 --> 29:21.080
A woman I didn't know.

29:21.080 --> 29:26.080
I saw Tony look down into the woman's face.

29:26.080 --> 29:30.080
He looks at me like that, I thought.

29:30.080 --> 29:34.080
He stands near me like that.

29:34.080 --> 29:38.080
The woman's hair was black and very long.

29:38.080 --> 29:41.080
She was beautiful.

29:41.080 --> 29:46.080
She said something and put her hand on Tony's arm.

29:46.080 --> 29:49.080
Then I saw Tony walk to his front door.

29:49.080 --> 29:54.080
He looked back at the woman and said something to her.

29:54.080 --> 29:59.080
I knew he wanted her to go into the house with him.

29:59.080 --> 30:02.080
Don't go in, I thought.

30:02.080 --> 30:08.080
But she did go in and Tony closed the door.

30:08.080 --> 30:13.080
I went into my house and closed my door.

30:13.080 --> 30:18.080
I sat down and thought about James again.

30:18.080 --> 30:22.080
James always had lots of girlfriends.

30:22.080 --> 30:27.080
Does Tony want me and that woman?

30:27.080 --> 30:32.080
But I didn't know the answer.

30:32.080 --> 30:35.080
Chapter 5.

30:35.080 --> 30:39.080
Who is that woman?

30:39.080 --> 30:45.080
I didn't see Tony that evening and he didn't phone me.

30:45.080 --> 30:51.080
When I left for work the next day, his car wasn't there.

30:51.080 --> 30:55.080
Was he with that woman?

30:55.080 --> 30:57.080
Are you okay?

30:57.080 --> 31:01.080
Klaus asked me when I got to the restaurant.

31:01.080 --> 31:04.080
Yes, thank you. I said.

31:04.080 --> 31:09.080
I didn't want to talk to him about Tony and the woman.

31:09.080 --> 31:13.080
I didn't want to talk to anyone about them.

31:13.080 --> 31:18.080
But I thought about them a lot, all day.

31:18.080 --> 31:25.080
After work I went quickly back to Bridge Street, but not to my house.

31:25.080 --> 31:28.080
I went to Tony's house.

31:28.080 --> 31:33.080
Hi, he said when he came to the door.

31:33.080 --> 31:37.080
He looked tired and he didn't kiss me.

31:37.080 --> 31:39.080
Come in.

31:39.080 --> 31:42.080
We went into the living room.

31:42.080 --> 31:45.080
He had a cup of coffee on the table.

31:45.080 --> 31:48.080
Sorry, he said.

31:48.080 --> 31:51.080
Do you want something to drink?

31:51.080 --> 31:54.080
No, I said.

31:54.080 --> 31:59.080
I want to speak to you about yesterday.

31:59.080 --> 32:03.080
I saw you with a woman.

32:03.080 --> 32:06.080
Tony looked down.

32:06.080 --> 32:09.080
Oh, he said.

32:09.080 --> 32:12.080
I waited for him to speak.

32:12.080 --> 32:15.080
It isn't what you think, Stella.

32:15.080 --> 32:17.080
He said.

32:17.080 --> 32:19.080
I looked at him.

32:19.080 --> 32:22.080
Stella, that was Kathy.

32:22.080 --> 32:24.080
Tony said.

32:24.080 --> 32:26.080
I sat down.

32:26.080 --> 32:29.080
I didn't know what to say.

32:29.080 --> 32:32.080
She wanted to talk to me.

32:32.080 --> 32:34.080
About what?

32:34.080 --> 32:37.080
Tony didn't answer.

32:37.080 --> 32:41.080
I thought about the two of them in the street.

32:41.080 --> 32:44.080
Tony, I asked.

32:44.080 --> 32:48.080
Do you still love Kathy?

32:48.080 --> 32:50.080
He looked up at me.

32:50.080 --> 32:53.080
No, he said.

32:53.080 --> 32:56.080
Do you think that?

32:56.080 --> 33:00.080
I don't know what to think, I said.

33:00.080 --> 33:03.080
Tony took my hand.

33:03.080 --> 33:05.080
Oh, Stella.

33:05.080 --> 33:07.080
He said.

33:07.080 --> 33:11.080
Of course I don't still love Kathy.

33:11.080 --> 33:13.080
You don't?

33:13.080 --> 33:14.080
I asked.

33:14.080 --> 33:17.080
I looked into his eyes.

33:17.080 --> 33:21.080
James didn't like me to look into his eyes like that.

33:21.080 --> 33:24.080
But Tony looked back into my eyes.

33:24.080 --> 33:28.080
He didn't look away.

33:28.080 --> 33:32.080
Sometimes I want to hate Kathy.

33:32.080 --> 33:34.080
He told me.

33:34.080 --> 33:35.080
But I can't.

33:35.080 --> 33:38.080
She's Daisy's mother.

33:38.080 --> 33:42.080
I know you think about the time when you were a family.

33:42.080 --> 33:44.080
I told him.

33:44.080 --> 33:47.080
You, Kathy, and Daisy.

33:47.080 --> 33:50.080
Yes, he said.

33:50.080 --> 33:52.080
I do think about that.

33:52.080 --> 33:56.080
I think about it because of Daisy.

33:56.080 --> 34:01.080
But I don't want to be with Kathy now, Stella.

34:01.080 --> 34:04.080
I want to be with you.

34:04.080 --> 34:07.080
Now I couldn't look at him.

34:07.080 --> 34:11.080
I felt small and afraid.

34:11.080 --> 34:13.080
Do you?

34:13.080 --> 34:15.080
I asked.

34:15.080 --> 34:18.080
Yes, he said.

34:18.080 --> 34:20.080
You know I do.

34:20.080 --> 34:22.080
I like you, Stella.

34:22.080 --> 34:24.080
I like you a lot.

34:24.080 --> 34:28.080
Actually, I looked up at him again.

34:28.080 --> 34:30.080
Yes?

34:30.080 --> 34:33.080
He smiled at me.

34:33.080 --> 34:37.080
Actually, I think I love you, Stella.

34:37.080 --> 34:39.080
No.

34:39.080 --> 34:42.080
I know I love you.

34:42.080 --> 34:46.080
I was happy again.

34:46.080 --> 34:49.080
Oh, Tony, I said.

34:49.080 --> 34:52.080
I love you, too.

34:52.080 --> 34:55.080
Come here, he said.

34:55.080 --> 34:58.080
And he kissed me.

34:58.080 --> 35:03.080
But I knew there was still something wrong.

35:03.080 --> 35:12.080
Kathy came here yesterday because she wanted to tell me something, he said.

35:12.080 --> 35:16.080
She and Cameron want to live in Scotland.

35:16.080 --> 35:19.080
They want to buy a house there.

35:19.080 --> 35:24.080
And they want to take Daisy with them.

35:24.080 --> 35:26.080
I looked at him.

35:26.080 --> 35:30.080
Oh, Tony, I said.

35:30.080 --> 35:33.080
She can't do that.

35:33.080 --> 35:36.080
Tony looked down again.

35:36.080 --> 35:40.080
I think she can, he said.

35:40.080 --> 35:45.080
She's Daisy's mother, and Daisy lives with her.

35:45.080 --> 35:48.080
Cameron has a new job in Scotland.

35:48.080 --> 35:52.080
And Kathy can get a job there as a teacher.

35:52.080 --> 35:58.080
But Daisy needs you, too, I said.

35:58.080 --> 36:01.080
Tony couldn't answer for a minute.

36:01.080 --> 36:04.080
He was too sad.

36:04.080 --> 36:08.080
Then he tried to smile.

36:08.080 --> 36:13.080
I don't know what to do, Stella, he said.

36:13.080 --> 36:17.080
I just don't know what to do.

36:17.080 --> 36:21.080
We can speak to someone who can help us.

36:21.080 --> 36:24.080
A lawyer, I said.

36:24.080 --> 36:26.080
We can stop her.

36:26.080 --> 36:29.080
That's what we can do.

36:29.080 --> 36:32.080
Tony looked at me.

36:32.080 --> 36:35.080
We can try, he said.

36:35.080 --> 36:45.080
Chapter 6, a family again.

36:45.080 --> 36:50.080
So we went to see a lawyer, a Mrs. Scott.

36:50.080 --> 36:55.080
I can talk to Kathy's lawyer, she told us.

36:55.080 --> 36:59.080
And then we can go to the family court.

36:59.080 --> 37:01.080
She looked at Tony.

37:01.080 --> 37:08.080
But I must tell you, Mr. Bryant, it isn't going to be easy.

37:08.080 --> 37:15.080
The family courts often think a child needs to be with his or her mother.

37:15.080 --> 37:19.080
Daisy needs her father, too, I said.

37:19.080 --> 37:22.080
And Mrs. Scott smiled.

37:22.080 --> 37:24.080
Yes, she said.

37:24.080 --> 37:26.080
I know that.

37:26.080 --> 37:29.080
We can only try.

37:29.080 --> 37:32.080
Thank you, said Tony.

37:32.080 --> 37:35.080
Then we left.

37:35.080 --> 37:39.080
The next two days were not easy.

37:39.080 --> 37:46.080
Then Mrs. Scott phoned and said that the family court was next Tuesday.

37:46.080 --> 37:51.080
Daisy came to us the weekend before the family court.

37:51.080 --> 37:55.080
The weather was bad, so we watched TV.

37:55.080 --> 37:59.080
There was a film about horses on television.

37:59.080 --> 38:02.080
Daisy looked up at us.

38:02.080 --> 38:06.080
Cameron says I can have a horse when we live in Scotland.

38:06.080 --> 38:08.080
She said.

38:08.080 --> 38:12.080
He wants to teach me all about horses.

38:12.080 --> 38:15.080
That's nice, Tony said.

38:15.080 --> 38:18.080
But I knew he was sad.

38:18.080 --> 38:21.080
I took his hand.

38:21.080 --> 38:26.080
But I want you to teach me about horses, Daddy.

38:26.080 --> 38:28.080
Daisy said.

38:28.080 --> 38:33.080
When he heard that, Tony smiled.

38:33.080 --> 38:36.080
Can you teach me, Daddy?

38:36.080 --> 38:38.080
Daisy asked.

38:38.080 --> 38:41.080
Tony gave her a kiss.

38:41.080 --> 38:46.080
Yes, baby, he said.

38:46.080 --> 38:53.080
But that evening, when Daisy was in bed, Tony looked at me.

38:53.080 --> 38:56.080
What do I know about horses?

38:56.080 --> 38:59.080
He said, nothing.

38:59.080 --> 39:03.080
I only know about computers.

39:03.080 --> 39:06.080
No, you don't, I said.

39:06.080 --> 39:10.080
You know how to love Daisy.

39:10.080 --> 39:13.080
And that's what's important.

39:13.080 --> 39:16.080
He kissed me and smiled.

39:16.080 --> 39:22.080
I'm very happy I came to live next door to you, Stella Greenwood.

39:22.080 --> 39:24.080
He said.

39:24.080 --> 39:28.080
On Tuesday, we went to the family court.

39:28.080 --> 39:32.080
Kathy was there with her lawyer and Cameron.

39:32.080 --> 39:36.080
Daisy was at home with Kathy's mother.

39:36.080 --> 39:39.080
Tony's hand was in mine.

39:39.080 --> 39:43.080
He didn't look over at Kathy or Cameron.

39:43.080 --> 39:47.080
Then the judge came into the court.

39:47.080 --> 39:51.080
He was a small man with gray hair.

39:51.080 --> 39:55.080
We were in the court for 30 minutes.

39:55.080 --> 40:01.080
Mrs Scott spoke for Tony and Kathy's lawyer spoke for Kathy.

40:01.080 --> 40:05.080
The judge listened and he asked some questions.

40:05.080 --> 40:08.080
Mrs Scott and Kathy's lawyer answered them.

40:08.080 --> 40:16.080
Then the judge looked at us and he said what we didn't want him to say.

40:16.080 --> 40:20.080
I'm sorry, Mr Bryant.

40:20.080 --> 40:23.080
I think that's all I heard him say.

40:23.080 --> 40:31.080
I just sat next to Tony and thought, no, no, no, no.

40:31.080 --> 40:35.080
Tony put his head in his hands.

40:35.080 --> 40:41.080
He didn't say anything, but I knew he was angry.

40:41.080 --> 40:48.080
When the judge and the lawyers left the court, Kathy came over to talk to Tony.

40:48.080 --> 40:51.080
But he didn't want to look at her.

40:51.080 --> 40:58.080
You can still see Daisy at any time, Tony, she told him.

40:58.080 --> 41:00.080
But he didn't answer.

41:00.080 --> 41:04.080
Then Kathy left with Cameron.

41:04.080 --> 41:07.080
I sat there next to Tony.

41:07.080 --> 41:11.080
I didn't know what to say to him.

41:11.080 --> 41:17.080
But then I thought about what Janet always said to me.

41:17.080 --> 41:21.080
When you want to do something, just do it.

41:21.080 --> 41:23.080
Don't stop and think.

41:23.080 --> 41:25.080
Don't wait.

41:25.080 --> 41:28.080
Just do it.

41:28.080 --> 41:32.080
And I knew what I wanted to do.

41:32.080 --> 41:37.080
Tony, I said, look at me.

41:37.080 --> 41:40.080
His face was white.

41:40.080 --> 41:44.080
I took his hands and looked into his eyes.

41:44.080 --> 41:48.080
Look, I said.

41:48.080 --> 41:55.080
There are computers in Scotland and lots of restaurants.

41:55.080 --> 41:57.080
What are you saying?

41:57.080 --> 41:59.080
He asked.

41:59.080 --> 42:01.080
I smiled.

42:01.080 --> 42:05.080
I'm saying we can live near Daisy.

42:05.080 --> 42:10.080
I'm saying we can go to Scotland.

42:10.080 --> 42:13.080
Tony smiled at me.

42:13.080 --> 42:16.080
A big smile.

42:16.080 --> 42:19.080
Me and you, he said.

42:19.080 --> 42:22.080
Yes, I said.

42:22.080 --> 42:27.080
Me, you and Daisy too.

42:27.080 --> 42:32.080
And in January, that's what we did.

42:32.080 --> 42:35.080
We went to live in Scotland.

42:35.080 --> 42:43.080
I got a job as a chef at a hotel and Tony got a good job with computers.

42:43.080 --> 42:49.080
And Daisy, well, we see her every weekend.

42:49.080 --> 42:54.080
She's teaching Tony about horses.

42:57.080 --> 43:15.080
Here's the beginning of another book at this level.

43:15.080 --> 43:19.080
Bad Love by Sue Leather.

43:19.080 --> 43:23.080
I met Dr. Jack Daly in August.

43:23.080 --> 43:26.080
It was a Saturday afternoon.

43:26.080 --> 43:31.080
I was at a party in Denver at my friend Judy Kaplan's house.

43:31.080 --> 43:35.080
We were in the backyard and it was hot.

43:35.080 --> 43:39.080
It's always hot in the summer in Denver.

43:39.080 --> 43:42.080
It was a good party.

43:42.080 --> 43:48.080
About 50 people were there and there were drinks and good food.

43:48.080 --> 43:53.080
I walked around the backyard and talked to people.

43:53.080 --> 43:56.080
I had a drink and tried some food.

43:56.080 --> 44:00.080
And then I met Jack Daly.

44:00.080 --> 44:03.080
Hi, he said.

44:03.080 --> 44:06.080
He had black hair and blue eyes.

44:06.080 --> 44:08.080
My name's Jack.

44:08.080 --> 44:10.080
Jack Daly.

44:10.080 --> 44:12.080
Hi, I said.

44:12.080 --> 44:13.080
I'm Flick.

44:13.080 --> 44:15.080
Flick Lane.

44:15.080 --> 44:17.080
We talked a little.

44:17.080 --> 44:25.080
He told me he was a doctor and that he worked at the University of Colorado Hospital in Denver.

44:25.080 --> 44:27.080
What about you?

44:27.080 --> 44:28.080
He asked me.

44:28.080 --> 44:31.080
I'm a detective, I said.

44:31.080 --> 44:33.080
Denver Police Department.

44:33.080 --> 44:35.080
Oh, a cop.

44:35.080 --> 44:37.080
He said with a smile.

44:37.080 --> 44:40.080
He had very white teeth.

44:40.080 --> 44:43.080
I smiled back at him.

44:43.080 --> 44:45.080
Yeah, I said.

44:45.080 --> 44:46.080
A cop.

44:46.080 --> 44:49.080
So where's your police car?

44:49.080 --> 44:50.080
He said.

44:50.080 --> 44:51.080
That's my car.

44:51.080 --> 44:52.080
Over there.

44:52.080 --> 44:53.080
I said.

44:53.080 --> 44:58.080
It's the red 1957 Chevrolet.

44:58.080 --> 45:00.080
A 57 Chevy.

45:00.080 --> 45:03.080
That's a beautiful car.

45:03.080 --> 45:04.080
He said.

45:04.080 --> 45:07.080
I love old Chevy's.

45:07.080 --> 45:10.080
We talked some more about cars.

45:10.080 --> 45:13.080
Then, okay, he said.

45:13.080 --> 45:16.080
Now tell me more about you.

45:16.080 --> 45:18.080
Well, I said.

45:18.080 --> 45:22.080
My first name's, uh, Felicity.

45:22.080 --> 45:24.080
I laughed.

45:24.080 --> 45:25.080
Felicity.

45:25.080 --> 45:27.080
Yes, I said.

45:27.080 --> 45:29.080
My dad liked it.

45:29.080 --> 45:32.080
But please call me Flick.

45:32.080 --> 45:34.080
We talked a little more.

45:34.080 --> 45:39.080
After some minutes he said, well, I'm leaving now, Flick.

45:39.080 --> 45:42.080
Can I see you again sometime?

45:42.080 --> 45:44.080
He smiled again.

45:44.080 --> 45:47.080
He had a beautiful smile.

45:47.080 --> 45:49.080
I smiled too.

45:49.080 --> 45:55.080
Okay, sure, I said, and gave him my phone number.

45:55.080 --> 46:00.080
He walked slowly out of the backyard and I watched him.

46:00.080 --> 46:01.080
Tall and dark.

46:01.080 --> 46:04.080
Nice, I thought.

46:04.080 --> 46:08.080
Later, after the party, I talked to Judy about daily.

46:08.080 --> 46:12.080
Tell me about the doctor, I said.

46:12.080 --> 46:14.080
Jack daily?

46:14.080 --> 46:16.080
Judy looked at me.

46:16.080 --> 46:18.080
He's a very good doctor.

46:18.080 --> 46:21.080
All the rich people go to him.

46:21.080 --> 46:25.080
You know, movie stars, sports stars.

46:25.080 --> 46:28.080
He's famous at the hospital.

46:28.080 --> 46:32.080
Judy is a doctor too, at the University Hospital.

46:32.080 --> 46:36.080
Oh, famous is he, I said.

46:36.080 --> 46:40.080
I don't often like famous people.

46:40.080 --> 46:43.080
Judy looked into my eyes.

46:43.080 --> 46:47.080
Oh, come on, Detective Lane, she said.

46:47.080 --> 46:49.080
You like him.

46:49.080 --> 46:51.080
I watched you with him.

46:51.080 --> 46:54.080
All the women like him.

